nobel-physics-1914 | 1914 Max von Laue | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1914/ | winner:Max von Laue description:for his discovery of the diffraction of X-rays by crystals
nobel-physics-1913 | 1913 Heike Kamerlingh Onnes | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1913/ | winner:Heike Kamerlingh Onnes description:for his investigations on the properties of matter at low temperatures which led, inter alia, to the production of liquid helium
nobel-physics-1912 | 1912 Nils Gustaf Dalén | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1912/ | winner:Nils Gustaf Dalén description:for his invention of automatic regulators for use in conjunction with gas accumulators for illuminating lighthouses and buoys
nobel-physics-1911 | 1911 Wilhelm Wien | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1911/ | winner:Wilhelm Wien description:for his discoveries regarding the laws governing the radiation of heat
nobel-physics-1910 | 1910 Johannes Diderik van der Waals | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1910/ | winner:Johannes Diderik van der Waals description:for his work on the equation of state for gases and liquids
nobel-physics-1909 | 1909 Guglielmo Marconi, Karl Ferdinand Braun | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1909/ | winner:Guglielmo Marconi, Karl Ferdinand Braun description:in recognition of their contributions to the development of wireless telegraphy
nobel-physics-1908 | 1908 Gabriel Lippmann | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1908/ | winner:Gabriel Lippmann description:for his method of reproducing colours photographically based on the phenomenon of interference
nobel-physics-1907 | 1907 Albert Abraham Michelson | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1907/ | winner:Albert Abraham Michelson description:for his optical precision instruments and the spectroscopic and metrological investigations carried out with their aid
nobel-physics-1906 | 1906 Joseph John Thomson | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1906/ | winner:Joseph John Thomson description:in recognition of the great merits of his theoretical and experimental investigations on the conduction of electricity by gases
nobel-physics-1905 | 1905 Philipp Eduard Anton von Lenard | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1905/ | winner:Philipp Eduard Anton von Lenard description:for his work on cathode rays
nobel-physics-1904 | 1904 Lord Rayleigh (John William Strutt) | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1904/ | winner:Lord Rayleigh (John William Strutt) description:for his investigations of the densities of the most important gases and for his discovery of argon in connection with these studies
nobel-physics-1903 | 1903 Antoine Henri Becquerel, Pierre Curie, Marie Curie, née Sklodowska | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1903/ | winner:Antoine Henri Becquerel, Pierre Curie, Marie Curie, née Sklodowska description:in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by his discovery of spontaneous radioactivity, in recognition of the extraordinary services they have rendered by their joint researches on the radiation phenomena discovered by Professor Henri Becquerel
nobel-physics-1902 | 1902 Hendrik Antoon Lorentz, Pieter Zeeman | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1902/ | winner:Hendrik Antoon Lorentz, Pieter Zeeman description:in recognition of the extraordinary service they rendered by their researches into the influence of magnetism upon radiation phenomena
nobel-physics-1901 | 1901 Wilhelm Conrad Röntgen | http://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/physics/laureates/1901/ | winner:Wilhelm Conrad Röntgen description:in recognition of the extraordinary services he has rendered by the discovery of the remarkable rays subsequently named after him
